==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Butte
<hw>Butte</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Butt</er> a bound.]</ety> <def>A detached low mountain, or high
rising abruptly from the general level of the surrounding plain; --
applied to peculiar elevations in the Rocky Mountain region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The creek . . . passes by two remarkable <qex>buttes</qex> of red
conglomerate.</q> <rj><qau>Ruxton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

